formattedAddress: Gallaeria Level, Marina Bay Sands (10 Bayfront Ave)

tip.text: Good food, but coffee really sucks. Love the fireplace, a life saver after long boat ride in the rain...
Definitely an all-in-one stop for Burmese food. A part from the typical fried stuffs (which you can find anywhere in Yangon), their noodles are really tasty and their tea is really flavourful!
Coffee is so-so, croissant is weird, unappealing taste and appearance. Wifi doesn't work too.
